label: Randomization block
definition: Each randomization block was made up of 9 adjacent clusters that were pair-matched by geography. Each cluster within the randomization block was randomly allocated to one of 7 intervention arms, including 2 clusters randomly allocated to the control arm.

label: Cluster ID
definition: The unit of randomization. A cluster consisted of 1 or more administrative villages. Two or more neighboring villages may be combined to create 1 cluster as long as the cluster of villages had at least 8 eligible pregnant women and shared a border.

label: Cluster study arm
definition: The actual randomized, blinded intervention assigned to the cluster.

label: Bruising during the last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had bruising (a negative control outcome measured to detect potential differential bias in symptom reporting) within in the last 2 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at  midline and endline.

label: Bruising during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had bruising (a negative control outcome measured to detect potential differential bias in symptom reporting) within in the last 7 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at midline  and endline.

label: Diarrhea case during the last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 2 days. To meet this definition of a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood using a 2-day recall. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 9-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 18-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Diarrhea case during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 7 days. To meet this definition of a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood using a 7-day recall. This variable was used in the primary analysis to improve power as there was no evidence for differential recall by arm. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 9-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 18-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.
